;; Project-level clj-kondo configuration.
;;
;; redundant-let is flagged at the default :warning level. In tests
;; we deliberately split (let [router …] (let [[provider model] …] …))
;; into an outer "fixture" binding and an inner "destructure the
;; result" binding because the two reads at very different layers of
;; abstraction. Merging into a single `let` saves three characters
;; and obscures intent. Demote to :info so verify.sh stays green
;; without rewriting every two-stage test.
{:linters
 {:redundant-let {:level :info}}}
